  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preparation Of The Resettlement Plan (Rp) For Households Affected By The Rehabilitation Of  Kelani Valley Railway Line  In Sri Lanka (Phase 01-Maradana To Homagama)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Purpose of the overall programme is to :Development of Quality transport facilities , improving railway tracks,signalling railway electrification etc.Provide better housing , infrastructure and other amenities for affected people due to rehabilitation of the railway line.Improve cityenvironmentProvide easy access to governanceReduce povertyMitigate/ Adapt climate change impactReduce disaster risk.The Purpose of the this project is: -To identify and support all affected group including women, youth and all other minorities.To make sure to collect all demographic, social, economic, physical and environment information and necessary data. To find out the potential resettlement options for affected people.To gather available livelihood options for affected people.To identify healthy, safety, resilience relocation sites with options for implementation.</narrative>
  </description>
